Greek nouns always have grammatical gender, and the three gender
categories are: masculine, feminine, and neuter.

There are two number categories in Greek: singular and plural.

Case identifies the function of a noun or pronoun. Greek has five
cases:

Case            Description
------------------------------------------------------
Accusative      Identifies the object of a sentence.
Dative          Expresses some relationship.
Genitive        Restricts the word in a sentence.
                Usually translated as "of/from ..."
Nominative      Identifies the subject of a sentence.
Vocative        The case of direct address.
